noun.description: A bone or cartilage in certain fishes, amphibians, reptiles, and birds, situated anterior to and sometimes fused with the coracoid bone of the pectoral girdle.

adjective.description: Situated anterior to the coracoid bone; specifically designating the bone or cartilage forming the precoracoid.

origin: Mid 19th century; earliest use found in William K. Parker (1823–1890), comparative anatomist and zoologist. From pre- + coracoid.
